Package neupaths.api

Class CellCluster

java.lang.Object
neupaths.api.CellCluster
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<Cell>
public class CellCluster extends Object implements Iterable<Cell>
Creates a cell cluster according to a cluster definition file.

A cell cluster is a collection of NeuPaths cell objects that can be manipulated as a single unit. The cells can be tightly-coupled (i.e. heavily interconnected), loosely-coupled (i.e. lightly interconnected) or independent.

A cluster definition file contains an XML schema that lists the cell definition file for each cell in the cluster. Logging and interval settings override the settings in the individual cell definition files. 

     <cell_cluster>
     <name></name>
     <cell_definitions>
         <cell_definition></cell_definition>
         ...
     </cell_definitions>
     <logging_enabled>true|false</logging_enabled>
     <trace_logging_enabled>true|false</trace_logging_enabled>
     <debug_logging_enabled>true|false</debug_logging_enabled>
     <runtime_logging_enabled>true|false</runtime_logging_enabled>
     <subscription_refresh_interval_ms></subscription_refresh_interval_ms>
     <duplicate_detection_interval_ms></duplicate_detection_interval_ms>
     <subscription_trace_interval_ms></subscription_trace_interval_ms>
     <crypto_key_file></crypto_key_file>
 </cell_cluster>

Cluster Definition Element Types

Element Name Description Element Path Element Type Opt? Default Example
cell_definition Pathname of a cell definition file cell_cluster/cell_definitions/cell_definition String No cfg/A_Cell.xml
crypto_key_file Pathname of file containing crypto secret key. cell_cluster/crypto_key_file String Yes null cfg/stim_key.dat
debug_logging_enabled Indicates if logging of EventType.DEBUG events is enabled. cell_cluster/debug_logging_enabled Boolean: "true" or "false" Yes false
duplicate_detection_interval_ms Length of duplicate detection window (millisecs). cell_cluster/duplicate_detection_interval_ms Numeric (long) Yes 1000
logging_enabled Indicates if cell logging is enabled. cell_cluster/logging_enabled Boolean: "true" or "false" Yes true
runtime_logging_enabled Indicates if logging of EventType.RUNTIME events is enabled. cell_cluster/runtime_logging_enabled Boolean: "true" or "false" Yes false
subscription_refresh_interval_ms Interval at which cell's subscriptions are refreshed (millisecs). cell_cluster/subscription_refresh_interval_ms Numeric (long) Yes 1500
subscription_trace_interval_ms Interval at which cell's current subscriptions are reported via EventType.TRACE events (millisecs). cell_cluster/subscription_trace_interval_ms Numeric (long) Yes 0
trace_logging_enabled Indicates if logging of EventType.TRACE events is enabled. cell_cluster/trace_logging_enabled Boolean: "true" or "false" Yes false
name Cluster name cell_cluster/name String No A_Cluster

    • setDuplicateDetectionInterval

      public void setDuplicateDetectionInterval(long millisecs)
      Sets the duplicate detection interval.

      The default is 1000 milliseconds (1 second.) The minimum is 250 milliseconds. Values less than the minimum will be automatically changed to the minimum value.

      Parameters:
      millisecs - Duration of interval in milliseconds

    • setSubscriptionRefreshInterval

      public void setSubscriptionRefreshInterval(long millisecs)
      Sets the subscription refresh interval.

      The default is 1500 milliseconds (1.5 seconds.) Values less than or equal to zero will disable automatic subscription refreshes. When disabled, the user must manually invoke publishSubscriptions() to advertise the cell's subscriptions.

      Parameters:
      millisecs - Duration of interval in milliseconds

    • setSubscriptionTraceInterval

      public void setSubscriptionTraceInterval(long millisecs)
      Sets the subscription trace interval.

      When enabled, the cell's nucleus reports the subscriptions it has registered in an EventType.TRACE log event each interval. Values less than or equal to zero disable subscription tracing. The value is zero by default, meaning this feature must be specifically enabled.

      Parameters:
      millisecs - Duration of interval in milliseconds

    • publishSubscriptions

      public void publishSubscriptions()
      Advertises the cell's subscriptions to the cell system. This method can be used when subscription refresh has been turned off. It should only be invoked after the cell has been started.

    • start

      public void start()
      Starts the cluster. Cells will be started in the order they were defined in the cluster definition file.

    • pause

      public void pause()
      Pause the cluster. Cells will be paused in the order they were defined in the cluster definition file.

    • resume

      public void resume()
      Resume the cluster. Cells will be resumed in the order they were defined in the cluster definition file.

    • stop

      public void stop()
      Stops the cluster. Cells will be stopped in the reverse order they were defined in the cluster definition file.
